If Penn and Teller
are incorrect about

01:17.377 --> 01:18.878
how a trick is done,

01:18.912 --> 01:20.647
they give up a slot
in their show

01:20.680 --> 01:23.316
and a shiny new
"Fool Us" trophy.

01:23.349 --> 01:26.186
Let's see how they do
against tonight's first act.

01:28.688 --> 01:31.591
- My dad is from Iran,
my mom is from Afghanistan,

01:31.624 --> 01:35.061
and they can came here
to live the American dream.

01:35.095 --> 01:37.697
My dad started
an Italian restaurant,

01:37.730 --> 01:39.899
in Texas of all places.

01:39.933 --> 01:42.735
This was the place my mom
and my dad got married in.

01:42.769 --> 01:45.171
One night, my dad
was locking up the doors

01:45.205 --> 01:47.941
so he could come see us,
his family.

01:47.974 --> 01:52.712
As he was walking to his car,
he got met by three masked men.

01:52.745 --> 01:55.081
And they killed my father.

01:55.115 --> 01:57.117
I was one when that happened.

01:57.150 --> 02:01.521
And my family kept it a secret
for me for years.

02:01.554 --> 02:04.491
So it's not surprising
I got into magic

02:04.524 --> 02:08.795
because magic is an art form
about secrets.

02:08.828 --> 02:10.830
But magic also taught me
that when you have a gift

02:10.864 --> 02:13.733
that is in you and you
give it out into the world,

02:13.766 --> 02:16.169
then really you become the
hero in somebody else's story.

02:16.202 --> 02:18.571
And to me, that's real magic.

02:18.605 --> 02:21.374
Whenever I get to share
what I do with the world,

02:21.407 --> 02:24.144
I just imagine
that my dad is behind me

02:24.177 --> 02:27.580
just whispering
that he's proud of me.

02:27.614 --> 02:30.183
Penn and Teller,
I'm gonna share it with you

02:30.216 --> 02:32.185
something quite amazing
tonight.

02:32.218 --> 02:34.888
And I know my dad
would be proud.

02:34.921 --> 02:38.324
[cheers and applause]

02:38.358 --> 02:41.394
- Stand back and make way
for Zak Mirz.

02:41.427 --> 02:43.897
[cheers and applause]

02:43.930 --> 02:46.432
- My first trick is done.

02:46.466 --> 02:51.404
Did you guys catch it?
Did you see it?

02:51.437 --> 02:53.273
- Oh, no.

02:53.306 --> 02:56.009
- I got this past security.

02:56.042 --> 02:58.178
- Oh, I thought I was
gonna like you.

02:58.211 --> 02:59.579
[laughter]

02:59.612 --> 03:01.314
- Sorry about the table,

03:01.347 --> 03:02.715
Alyson.
- Mm-hmm.

03:02.749 --> 03:04.951
- You probably see this
as a really sharp knife.

03:04.984 --> 03:07.453
I see it as a magic wand.

03:07.487 --> 03:09.489
