one for you, one for me.

05:18.051 --> 05:21.688
And you're gonna hover
that knife over that card.

05:21.721 --> 05:27.026
You're gonna go straight down
and slowly pick up.

05:27.060 --> 05:28.361
By the way, that stab's on you.

05:28.394 --> 05:30.530
So we're gonna split the bill
for the table.

05:30.563 --> 05:31.731
[laughter]

05:31.764 --> 05:33.866
But let's see how you did.

05:33.900 --> 05:37.570
♪ ♪

05:37.603 --> 05:41.140
Just make sure you stab
through more than one card

05:41.174 --> 05:44.043
and less than 52, but
don't overthink any of this.

05:44.077 --> 05:48.181
Just channel in your inner...

05:48.214 --> 05:50.650
psychopath and you'll do great.
[laughter]

05:50.683 --> 05:54.887
So whenever you're ready,
go ahead and take a stab at it.

05:54.921 --> 05:56.255
- Stab the deck?
- Yeah.

05:56.289 --> 05:59.025
♪ ♪

05:59.058 --> 06:00.727
Hold.

06:00.760 --> 06:02.628
All right. It's okay.
All right. Here's the thing.

06:02.662 --> 06:04.597
If you would've stabbed
a little bit harder,

06:04.630 --> 06:07.667
you could have stabbed
to any one of these cards.

06:07.700 --> 06:11.037
Penn, what was the name
of your card?

06:11.070 --> 06:13.439
- Three of spades.
- Three of spades.

06:13.473 --> 06:17.677
♪ ♪

06:17.710 --> 06:19.212
[audience exclaims]

06:19.245 --> 06:22.048
The three of spades.
[applause]

06:22.081 --> 06:25.385
- Zak Mirz.

06:25.418 --> 06:27.787
- Thank you so much.
Thank you so, so much.

06:27.820 --> 06:29.188
- How did you come up
with this?

06:29.222 --> 06:31.824
And do all your tricks
involve weapons?

06:31.858 --> 06:34.560
- Yeah. Okay. So funny story.
I actually created this trick

06:34.594 --> 06:36.396
because I got married
five years ago.

06:36.429 --> 06:39.065
And I go on tour a lot
and my wife was like, you know,

06:39.098 --> 06:40.867
I just kind of want, like,
a pocket knife,

06:40.900 --> 06:42.368
just in case, just in case.

06:42.402 --> 06:43.736
So we got her pocket knife
and I'm like,

06:43.770 --> 06:45.304
I kinda want
a pocket knife as well.

06:45.338 --> 06:47.573
So I bought one for myself.

06:47.607 --> 06:49.409
And I was like, what kind
of tricks could I do with it?

06:49.442 --> 06:51.911
So I kinda like created this,
and it's been a lot of fun.

06:51.944 --> 06:55.081
So people don't know me
as, like, the magician anymore.

06:55.114 --> 06:57.350
They know me
as, like, the knife guy.

06:57.383 --> 06:58.584
- Yeah. I'm just gonna
always think of you

06:58.618 --> 06:59.886
as the guy not to hug.

06:59.919 --> 07:01.587
- Yeah. Yeah.

07:01.621 --> 07:04.690
- So what would it mean
for you to fool these guys?

07:04.724 --> 07:07.627
- I'm just excited.
I got invited to the party.

07:07.660 --> 07:09.162
It's just such an honor
to be here right now.

07:09.195 --> 07:10.997
I can't really
put it into worlds.

07:11.030 --> 07:13.366
I know it's gonna be, like,
so quick as well.

07:13.399 --> 07:16.135
So I'm just trying to process
this whole experience.

07:16.169 --> 07:19.005
So I don't forget it.
So I'm just so grateful

07:19.038 --> 07:20.840
that I'm even talking
to you right now

07:20.873 --> 07:23.876
and talking
to Penn and Teller as well.

07:23.910 --> 07:26.279
It's very intimidating,
by the way.

07:26.312 --> 07:28.781
- You're a natural.
- Oh, thank you so much.

07:28.815 --> 07:32.652
- Okay, Zak, it's time to see
if you fooled Penn and Teller.

07:32.685 --> 07:34.454
- Hey, Zak.
- Hey, Penn.

07:34.487 --> 07:37.623
- You kind of wormed your way
into our heart right away

07:37.657 --> 07:40.526
because, one of the things
on this show that people

07:40.560 --> 07:42.662
are always trying to do is make
card tricks interesting,

07:42.695 --> 07:44.397
which is always tough.

07:44.430 --> 07:46.999
And you may not know this,
but one of our first big,

07:47.033 --> 07:49.001
big appearances
was on "Letterman"

07:49.035 --> 07:51.537
and we did a card stab.

07:51.571 --> 07:53.206
That's what we did.

07:53.239 --> 07:56.342
It supposedly went wrong and
the knife went through my hand,

07:56.375 --> 07:58.211
with the selected card
on my hand.

07:58.244 --> 08:00.646
And my hand came up
and you know,

08:00.680 --> 08:02.615
you're always told not to touch
David Letterman,

08:02.648 --> 08:03.850
not to get near him.

08:03.883 --> 08:05.585
He's very squeamish about that.

08:05.618 --> 08:07.353
And my hand came up
with the fake blood,

08:07.386 --> 08:09.789
it went right across his face.
[laughter]

08:09.822 --> 08:11.991
But he had us
on another 20 times,

08:12.024 --> 08:13.493
so I guess it was okay.
- Yeah.

08:13.526 --> 08:17.463
- But we love the idea
of doing a card stab.

08:17.497 --> 08:19.298
We knew right away

08:19.332 --> 08:21.467
that the Force wasn't quite
with you the way you wanted.

08:21.501 --> 08:22.668
- Yeah.
- When you started.

08:22.702 --> 08:24.470
And we followed that.

08:24.504 --> 08:29.509
And we think that,
you just got

08:29.542 --> 08:33.212
a shim metal plate in the card

08:33.246 --> 08:36.449
under the card
that was selected.

08:36.482 --> 08:39.685
And that stopped.
And that's where the card was.

08:39.719 --> 08:41.487
If that's not the way
you did it, then you fooled us.

08:41.521 --> 08:43.623
We're pretty sure
that's the way you did it.

08:43.656 --> 08:48.528
So you had a little metal plate
or something in there. Right?

08:48.561 --> 08:52.398
- If I understand you
correctly, like a metal plate--

08:52.431 --> 08:53.666
- Yeah.

08:53.699 --> 08:54.700
At the bottom.
- The card that was made--

08:54.734 --> 08:56.202
- Sorry,
this is going really fast.

08:56.235 --> 08:58.471
So I'm so sorry, but it
it's a, like a metal plate.

08:58.504 --> 08:59.572
- One card was a metal

08:59.605 --> 09:01.474
that stopped
the knife going that far?

09:01.507 --> 09:04.310
- Yeah. If I understand
what you're saying,

09:04.343 --> 09:07.580
that's--that's, um,
that's not it.

09:07.613 --> 09:09.615
[all gasping]

09:09.649 --> 09:12.351
- Huh? Huh?
[laughter]

09:12.385 --> 09:14.186
- Well, I have to move
this over here

09:14.220 --> 09:15.588
and say that
you have fooled us.

09:15.621 --> 09:17.123
- Oh, my God.

09:17.156 --> 09:18.925
- Take it off, take it off.
- Okay, okay.

09:18.958 --> 09:20.860
- Thank you so much.
Thank you, thank you.

09:20.893 --> 09:22.662
- Now you're huggable.
- Thank you. Thank you.

09:22.695 --> 09:24.830
Oh, my gosh.
Thank you so much.

09:24.864 --> 09:26.632
- Look at that behind you.
- Thank you so much. Thank you.

09:26.666 --> 09:29.201
Oh, my goodness.
Oh, my gosh.

09:29.235 --> 09:32.104
Thank you so much, guys.
- Congratulations.

09:32.138 --> 09:34.707
- Thank you so much.
- I'm going to hug you now.

09:34.740 --> 09:38.044
- Mr. Penn, thank you so much.
Thank you so much, guys.

09:38.077 --> 09:40.012
- Oh, dear.
- Wow.

09:40.046 --> 09:41.981
- Zak Mirz!
- Thank you.

