10:15.247 --> 10:17.583
Let's bring out
our next challenger.

10:20.086 --> 10:22.355
- Everything I do
ends up in magic.

10:22.388 --> 10:24.023
I puppeteer,

10:24.056 --> 10:25.858
I do stilt works.

10:25.891 --> 10:30.262
I did fire shows, too,
until it burned my crazy hair.

10:30.296 --> 10:32.231
Robotics,
that's my new passion.

10:32.264 --> 10:34.066
[laughs]

10:34.100 --> 10:35.701
Like all performers,

10:35.735 --> 10:39.705
I will do anything it takes
to get your attention.

10:41.207 --> 10:43.943
I'm severely dyslexic, also.

10:43.976 --> 10:48.214
I grew up and I could not read
a book to pass my time.

10:48.247 --> 10:50.082
Magic taught me
to amuse myself

10:50.116 --> 10:52.518
and then how to amuse others.

10:52.551 --> 10:56.355
Actually, I think my magic
benefited from dyslexia.

10:56.389 --> 11:00.059
It surprises people
by following its own path.

11:00.092 --> 11:03.195
I don't know how to do magic
in a way they have seen before.

11:03.229 --> 11:05.398
This is how I hope
to fool Penn and Teller.

11:05.431 --> 11:07.533
I had to learn it my own way.

11:08.534 --> 11:11.337
[cheers and applause]

11:13.039 --> 11:15.141
