from dyslexia. How?

15:33.732 --> 15:36.001
- I actually learned
everything from books,

15:36.035 --> 15:38.037
but I misunderstood
everything.

15:38.070 --> 15:40.673
So I did it a different way

15:40.706 --> 15:43.175
just because
I misunderstood everything.

15:43.208 --> 15:45.911
- Wow. Well, that's pretty
impressive then.

15:45.945 --> 15:51.083
- Yeah. It's solving problems.
That's my thing.

15:51.116 --> 15:52.751
- Yeah.

15:52.785 --> 15:56.522
Okay, John-Henry, let's see if
you've fooled Penn and Teller.

15:56.555 --> 16:00.960
- Hey John-Henry. Boy, we got
so much good stuff to say.

16:00.993 --> 16:03.996
I gotta go pretty fast.
We just loved everything.

16:04.029 --> 16:06.799
If you wanted to do
a theatrical production

16:06.832 --> 16:08.434
and you wanted quotes,

16:08.467 --> 16:11.036
First thing I said was,
"That was just perfect."

16:11.070 --> 16:12.638
